definitions.definition: to force someone to leave a particular place:
examples: A number of fans had been ejected from the bar for causing trouble.

definitions.definition: to order a sports player to leave the playing area during a game because they have broken a rule
to leave an aircraft in an emergency using an ejection seat
to come out of a machine when a button is pressed, or to make something do this:
examples: How do you eject the tape?
